1. If you don't have a venv directory in your root directory
    -Use command "python -m venv venv" to create the virtual environment directory

2. Activate your virtual environment
    -Linux/macOS: "venv/bin/activate"
    -Windows: ".\venv\Scripts\activate"

3. Make sure you have the correct version of pip
    -Run this command to update "python.exe -m pip install --upgrade pip"

4. Make sure you have the correct setuptools version
    -Run command "pip install --upgrade setuptools"

5. Now when you open app.py you should be getting a warning about packages needing to be installed.
    -Use command "pip install -r requirements.txt"
